que 1.JPG|Husein-pasha's mosque, [[Pljevlja]]\nImage:Crkva Svetih apostola Petra i Pavla (Petrova crkva), Novi Pazar, Srbija.jpg|[[Church of the Holy Apostles Peter and Paul, Ras]] near [[Novi Pazar]], 8-9th century\nImage:Stari Ras.jpg|[[Stari Ras]] fortress near [[Novi Pazar]], 8th century\nImage:\u0110ur\u0111evi stupovi, November 2005.jpg|[[\u0110ur\u0111evi Stupovi]] monastery, near [[Novi Pazar]], 12th century\nImage:Meister von Mileseva 001.jpg|[[White Angel]], fresco from [[Mile\u0161eva monastery]] near [[Prijepolje]], c. 1235\nImage:Manastir Sopocani.jpg|[[Sopo\u0107ani]] monastery, 13th century\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bosniaks]]\n* [[Bosniaks of Serbia]]\n* [[Bosniaks of Montenegro]]\n* [[Flag of Sand\u017eak]]\n* [[Geography of Serbia]]\n* [[Geography of Montenegro]]\n\n== References ==\n\n=== Notes ===\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|last=Banac |first=Ivo |year=1988 |title=With Stalin Against Tito: Cominformist Splits in Yugoslav Communism |location=Ithaca, NY |publisher=Cornell University Press |isbn=0801421861 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=G\u00f3rak-Sosnowska |first=Katarzyna |year=2011 |title=Muslims in Poland and Eastern Europe: Widening the European Discourse on Islam |location=Warszaw |publisher=Faculty of Oriental Studies, University of Warszaw |isbn=8390322951 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Had\u017ei\u0161ehovi\u0107 |first1=Munevera |last2=Butler |first2=Thomas J. |last3=Risaluddin |first3=Saba |year=2003 |title=A Muslim Woman in Tito's Yugoslavia |location=College Station, TX |publisher=Texas A&M University Press |isbn=1585443042 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Jeli\u0107 |first1=Ivan |last2=Strugar |first2=Novak |year=1985 |title=War and revolution in Yugoslavia, 1941-1945 |location=Belgrade |publisher=Socialist Thought and Practice |ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130712163204/http://sandzaknews.net/ News from Sand\u017eak sa